p: The variations in circRNA expression between Torin 1-treated SKOV3 cells and NC (SKOV3 cells mixed with DMSO) were assessed using scatter plot (Fig. 1B). GO analysis found that these differentially expressed circRNAs participated in many cellular processes, including microtubule binding, actin filament binding, GTPase activator activity, and activities of activators for protein serine/threonine kinase (Fig. 1C). The pathway analysis found that the differentially expressed circRNAs participated in TGF-Î² signal transduction pathway, Wnt signal transduction pathway, Rap1 signal transduction pathway, Ras signal transduction pathway, and so on (Fig. 1D).
